<p>Since <a href="#fischers-london-yes-but">eating at Fischers's</a>, I've been inclined to make Schnitzel. This is my attempt.</p>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>Salt and ground black pepper.</li>
<li>All-purpose flour.</li>
<li>Eggs (beaten).</li>
<li>Bread crumbs (natural).</li>
<li>Oil.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Preparation</h2>
<ul>
<li>Flatten the pork/chicken/veal.</li>
<li>Season (salt and pepper).</li>
<li>Heat pan with a generous amount of oil.</li>
<li>Dip into flour -&gt; egg -&gt; bread crumbs.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Garnish</h2>
<ul>
<li>Anchovies.</li>
<li>Capers.</li>
</ul>
